    "For long-duration missions, the inevitably incoming thermal energy (e.g., due to radiation) and the different gravitational levels result in complex multiphase configurations 26.",
    "After longer times, for example, during longcoasting phases, the liquid propellant reaches saturation conditions.",
    "Small overheats from the solid walls may lead to pool boiling.",
    "Small superheats due to depressurization may lead to pool cavitation.",
    "Both effects lead to the formation and the growth of bubbles (see Fig. 1) 49."
